<br>
Shamans and Bards, I must say, are the most versatile classes... Well. Maybe a druid more-so then a shaman. But high-end, the Shaman is a lot more concentrated in the slow, which gives them the edge over the druid... That said, if the person cannot decide what to play, or wants to do what is best for you, (Although I'd highly encourage them to play 'whatever sounds cool. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), Bard and Shaman are probably your best bet, considering how much they're wanted, and how they would fit in that group...<br>
<br>
For that group, a bard can bring... Downtime Heal song, with Bandaids. Haste. AC. Damage Shield. Transportation (Seloes is crazy fast.) Decent slows and snares. Some DDs and DoTs, as well as their melee damage, which, along side their song damage, is not too shabby. For those pesky casters, you've got resists. And of course, for CC, you've got both the most reliable mes and charm in the game (so says my Bard friend <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
A Shaman can bring downtime and battle heals, superb slows, stat buffs, as well as the Talisman which is a good hp spell, minor haste... Good dots, a pet... Root, for some minor CC... Bleh, can't think. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Both are great group and raid classes. Both would make a great addition to the group. Both are badass ... well. That's debateable. &lt;evil grin&gt; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ughitming.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghitming</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 12:08:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22882.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nettechwest.com/eq/claw.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Shaman for indoors.  Slow, DoT, Buff, Regen and spot heals are nice.<br>
